onceptualizing history and mimesis as a means of representing reality-to show how Istanbul shaped Mimesis and to understand Turkey's humanist reform movement as a type of cultural mimesis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aHumanismzTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish refugeeszTurkeyzIstanbul. 0aLiterary historianszTurkeyzIstanbul. 0aPhilologistszTurkeyzIstanbul. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh1 aHolbrook, Victoria08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804775755zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804775755423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804775755.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles